title: A1466 820-00165-A no disk
message:
Hi,

I have an A1466 820-00165-A that doesn't recognize the SSD.

Already tried several other SSD with the same result. Does this model use to have the CPU problem? How can I test it?

Can you help?

title: A1466 820-00165-A no disk
message:
Any history available?
Check U3740 voltages, w/ and w/o SSD connected.

title: A1466 820-00165-A no disk
message:
Hi,
No history. Client says that it stoped working.

U3740  with SSD connected:
1 = 3.4V
2 = 0.998V
3 = 3.287V
4= 0V
6= 0.633V
7= 0V
8= 3.284V

U3740  w/o SSD connected:
1 = 3.4V
2 = 1V
3 = 3.287V
4= 0V
6= 0.627V
7= 3.3V
8= 3.284V

title: A1466 820-00165-A no disk
message:
Check R1620/96; only one must be used.
You can try to force the power enable soldering a lower value.
Use R8070, as last resort...
